createSegTip1: Creating segments allows you to clearly seperate portions of your performance.
createSegTip2: For example you can create a segment for each quarter or period of a performance and easily compare the data.
createSegTip3: You can add up to 6 segments per performance.
createSegTip4: You can select a segment to edit or delete from this panel.
createSegTip5: Simply click finish when you’re done. Don’t worry, if you made a mistake you can come back and edit your segments at any time.
createSegTip6: You can also edit the start and end times here or using the pop-up slider.
createSegTip7: Alternatively use this panel to quickly select and add pre-defined intervals.
createSegTip8: You must name each segment. Using meaningful names makes analysing data easier.
createSegTip9: You can click and drag each segment to edit them precisely. Clicking a segment in the chart also selects it in the table below.
